The paper introduces a new ant-based method for clustering and pattern recognition, which involves self-organization and grid-based movement of ants. This method is inspired by Kohonen's Self-Organizing Maps, which are commonly used in neural networks and machine learning. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). Additionally, the paper involves clustering and pattern recognition, which are common topics in machine learning and artificial intelligence, making cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) likely sub-categories as well. The paper also mentions the use of grids and cells, which are common in computer vision and image processing, making cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) a possible sub-category. Finally, the paper involves natural-inspired algorithms, which are also common in natural language processing, making cs.CL (Computation and Language) a possible sub-category.
